        <span class="opacity-80 display-inline"> Camfecting is the criminal process by which a
          hacker breaks into a person's personal webcam
          with the goal of activating it without that person's
          consent. The first step in camfecting is to infect the
          computer. This infection usually occurs at the
          victim's own hands by downloading infected
          software (such as a Trojan horse). Through this
          software, the hacker gains access and can view
          anything and anyone within the field of view of the
          webcam. </span>
      </div>

